[{"id": "e637b682-e463-4cf6-a13f-cc763403b352", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: Hi. i was just given early beta access to lagoon. where should I start?\nASSISTANT: Hey! Welcome in. \ud83c\udf89\n\nOkay so here's the thing \u2014 Lagoon looks like a chat app, but it's really a **writing workspace** for long-form fiction and roleplay. The magic happens when you set up a character. That's where you should start.\n\n**First stop: Character Config**\n\nHit that character panel and you'll see:\n- **System Prompt** \u2014 who the character is, how they talk, what they know\n- **World Context** \u2014 background lore, setting details\n- **Author's Note** \u2014 instructions that get injected every turn (super useful for keeping the voice on track)\n- **Opening Line** \u2014 how they start the conversation\n\nFill those in, pick a provider (Ollama's free if you've got it running locally, otherwise you'll need an API key for Venice/Together/etc.), and start chatting.\n\n**After that, explore:**\n- **Anchors** \u2014 keyword triggers that inject lore when it's relevant (and track what's been \"revealed\" to the character)\n- **Style Overseer** \u2014 auto-review of responses with custom rules\n- **Writing tools** \u2014 every response has Fork, Nudge, Edit, Keep for Export\n\nDocs are here if you want the deep dive: https://genxennial.github.io/Lagoon/\n\nBut honestly? Just make a character and start writing. You'll figure out the rest as you go. That's kind of the whole point.\n\nWhat kind of stories are you looking to write?", "embedding": [-0.01301782950758934, -0.0984148234128952, 0.024963082745671272, -0.04930493235588074, -0.05711065232753754, -0.0036270974669605494, 0.06550498306751251, -0.01479280274361372, -0.011987389996647835, -0.05968335270881653, -0.023291023448109627, -0.08729524165391922, -0.049606651067733765, -0.004427049774676561, 0.05356893688440323, 0.018050430342555046, 0.09427988529205322, -0.06318826973438263, 2.4669883714523166e-05, -0.0055562052875757